The period of \(\cos(3\pi t)\) is \(T_1 = \frac{2\pi}{3\pi} = \frac{2}{3}\), and the period of \(\cos(5\pi t - 0.5\pi)\) is \(T_2 = \frac{2\pi}{5\pi} = \frac{2}{5}\).  
The fundamental period of the sum is the least common multiple of \(\frac{2}{3}\) and \(\frac{2}{5}\), which is \(2\) seconds.  

